epper then cook <b>10 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add spinach and pine nuts then stir in well with spatula."},{"content":"Increase oven temperature to 200°C."},{"content":"Slice off tops of potatoes and scoop out filling leaving 1 cm around edges. Fill with stuffing then sprinkle with reserved grated cheese. Place in an oven-proof dish then bake for 10 minutes (200°C) or until golden. Serve immediately."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Use the scooped out potato flesh to make mash.","Bake the sliced-off potato tops until crispy then serve with a dip."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","1h 20m","8 pieces"]}